# Git Commit Rules

- Commit messages must be concise and descriptive.
- NEVER include "Made-with: Cursor", "Made with Cursor", or any similar Cursor attribution in commit messages.
- Use conventional commit prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`.
- Write commit messages in English.
- Use `-F` (file-based) method for multi-line commit messages in PowerShell to avoid shell escaping issues.
